description: We had this tune from before we recorded "We Are". We called it "A Song" and played it without much of a structure and improvised lyrics in the Glassford St 13th Note a few times before letting it drop. It's really just Elaine's bass riff, which sounds pretty cool so long as the singer doesn't start playing "E" despite the clue in the name. After the scout hut party debacle it took a few months before i pulled together a proper structure for this and recorded it for John Peel in early 1996. The studio version  was used on the NME "C96" cassette, although now that i think of it, maybe its the studio demo version we gave them. The version we used on "Slain" got recorded the next year at KONK with the guitar I bought for ¬£25 in a junk shop.  The na-na's are ultra bratty and the words are mostly stupid. The bass part still sounds pretty cool though. (GK)
title: Urusei Yatsura Skull In Action(John Peel Session April 1996)
